  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Protection Assistance at Nimroz and Herat Border-Crossing Points and Transit Centers, and Access to Protection-Related Immediate Basic Needs in Provinces of Return for Undocumented Deportees to Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project focuses its efforts on ensuring protection of vulnerable undocumented deportees from Iran through enhanced collaboration with the Government of Afghanistan in protection screening and identification at border-crossing points; providing vulnerable deportees with protection support and assistance from border points to provinces of return; and provision of multi-purpose cash transfers in provinces of return to prevent returnees from resorting to negative coping mechanisms that could result in new protection risks. IOM also responds to these vulnerable returnees&apos; COVID-19 related health and protection needs through risk communication, distribution of personal protective equipment, health screenings and referrals, and national and provincial coordination.</narrative>
  </description>
